Program: A History of Ideas
Title: Theologian Giles Fraser on Altruism
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0639wy3
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 29 Jul 2015
Giles Fraser discusses gene theory versus altruism with playwright Tom Stoppard whose play The Hard Problem explores the extent to which our genes dictate human acts of love and kindness, and Armand Leroi, the evolutionary biologist who says we are merely programmed to carry out altruistic acts. Producer: Maggie Ayre. Show less